text: Budget Revision Request 2 - El Estero WWTF FOG Pilot Project
label: BODY

text: On February 17, 2010, City Council authorized AECOM to proceed with the design of a pilot Fats Oil
label: BODY

text: and Grease (FOG) receiving, handling, and injection station at the El Estero Wastewater Treatment
label: BODY

text: Plant (WWTP). Our approved scope includes plans and technical specifications for the site piping,
label: BODY

text: pumping, storage vessel, and local controls of the receiving and delivery system. We are also
label: BODY

text: contracted to provide limited construction phase support.
label: BODY

text: City staff has requested AECOM to include additional project features and engineering tasks to our
label: BODY

text: approved scope of work. The additional scope items requested are:
label: BODY

text: Design of a containment area surrounding the FOG processing area
label: BODY

text: Through our discussions with City staff, we have developed the following understanding of the
label: BODY

text: requested modifications to our Scope of Work.
label: BODY

text: Additional Task Item 1 - FOG Containment Facilities
label: BODY

text: AECOM will provide construction plans and specifications for a containment wall surrounding
label: BODY

text: the FOG processing area. Preliminary estimates indicate a concrete wall (25' x 25' x 3' high) will
label: BODY

text: be required to contain 150% of the volume of the FOG storage tank. The design will include
label: BODY

text: stairs with a handrail to access the containment area, and the containment area will feature
label: BODY

text: concrete flatwork within the entire contained area. Flatwork will be sloped to a sump. The
label: BODY

text: sump will be connected to a manually operated valve to allow periodic draining of collected
label: BODY

text: water to the cul-de-sac drain (see item 2 below). As discussed, pumps will be located within the
label: BODY

text: contained area. Truck offload equipment (rock trap, hose connection, etc.) will be located
label: BODY

text: outside the containment area. Per Staff request, our design will not feature a roof structure.
label: BODY

text: We have reviewed record drawing information provided by City staff and have not identified any
label: BODY

text: conflict with existing utilities in the area of the proposed containment area. We assume that no
label: BODY

text: such conflicts exist. The construction contractor will be responsible to identify and mitigate any
label: BODY

text: AECOM will provide construction plans and specifications for a gravity drain connection
label: BODY

text: (assumed 6 inch) between the proposed containment area and the existing cul-de-sac drain. We
label: BODY

text: will also connect the proposed FOG rock trap to the new drain to facilitate maintenance of the
label: BODY

text: screen. Seal water from the positive displacement pumps will also be directed to the drain.
label: BODY

text: We have assumed that adequate fall exists between the proposed containment area and the
label: BODY

text: existing drain, and that no conflicts exist along the alignment. Through discussions with plant
label: BODY

text: staff and our preliminary review of existing record drawings, we assume that the nearby utilities
label: BODY

text: (such as the plant outfall line) are adequately deep as to not impact the design of the proposed
label: BODY

text: We have budgeted 6 hours of time to further review existing as-built drawings to evaluate
label: BODY

text: conflicts and determine grade lines such as inverts at the existing cul-de-sac drain. If adequate
label: BODY

text: cover does not exist over the proposed drain line, a slurry trench may be recommended.
label: BODY

text: Additional Task Item 3 - Requested Revisions to Existing Work
label: BODY

text: To date AECOM has performed work beyond what was approved in our original scope and
label: BODY

text: budget (e.g. providing a reinforced concrete slab and seismic design, and participating in
label: BODY

text: additional meetings and coordination efforts). We have also evaluated various revisions to the
label: BODY

text: scope (additional digester piping, SCADA integration, and drainage improvements), analyzed
label: BODY

text: potential impacts to project cost, and provided an opinion of cost for each potential revision.
label: BODY

text: Additionally, upon review of the Preliminary Design Memo (submitted April 28, 2010),
label: BODY

text: significant modifications to the original scope of the project were requested by City staff. To
label: BODY

text: incorporate these requests, AECOM must abandon some work already completed, revise other
label: BODY

text: existing work, and perform new work not anticipated. These tasks include:
label: BODY

text: Performing additional electrical calculations and layout
label: BODY

text: Providing technical specs for a different tank and appurtenances,
label: BODY

text: Providing additional direction for controlling and programming two duplex pump
label: BODY

text: To accommodate the direction requested by City staff without eroding the approved budget for
label: BODY

text: the remaining work, AECOM is requesting additional budget of $4,277 to incorporate these
label: BODY

text: revisions. As always, work would be performed on a time-and-materials basis and will be billed
label: BODY

text: Additional Task Item 4 - Additional Construction Phase Support
label: BODY

text: Our approved Scope of Work includes limited construction phase support. We are currently
label: BODY

text: authorized to respond to four (4) RFIs, assist the City with examining bids, attend a pre-construction
label: BODY

text: meeting, and manage submittals. With the additional project components noted above, we are
label: BODY

text: requesting an increase in budget for additional submittal review and RFI response.
label: BODY

text: We are also authorized to be onsite for four (4) hours during the first day of field work, four (4)
label: BODY

text: hours during one progress visit during construction, and for four (4) hours for one final visit to
label: BODY

text: evaluate the near completed facilities. Our site visits are intended to monitor the overall
label: BODY

text: construction progress of the project and to address any major deficiencies encountered. Our
label: BODY

text: approved scope does not include construction management or construction observation where daily
label: BODY

text: activities are monitored and recorded. We are therefore not requesting additional budget to
label: BODY

text: manage the additional construction activities. If unforeseen site conditions or quality concerns arise
label: BODY

text: as construction proceeds, AECOM can perform additional support and site visits on an as-needed
label: BODY

text: time and materials basis to assist with resolving issues and developing solutions in the field. Any
label: BODY

text: additional services would be requested in writing for approval prior to the work being performed.
label: BODY

text: An hourly breakdown of these scope revisions can be seen on the attached worksheet (attached).
label: BODY

text: Please sign and return the enclosed copy of this letter, thereby enabling us to perform these
label: BODY

text: additional services on a time and materials basis.
